In this statement, the President sends his congratulations to those celebrating Polish Constitution Day, both in Poland and the United States. He acknowledges the significance of Poland's Constitution as an inspiration for democratic freedoms. The President also recognizes the contributions of Polish Americans to the national character of the United States and highlights the strong alliance between the two countries. He expresses condolences for the tragic loss of President Lech Kaczynski, First Lady Maria Kaczynska, and other leaders in a plane crash, and praises the resilience of the Polish people.